  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients suffering from congestive heart failure report reduced exercise capacity. This
      skeletal muscle dysfunction is also detectable when using small muscle groups which should
      not put any demand on the heart.

      We hypothesize that congestive heart failure has systemic effects that causes the skeletal
      muscle dysfunction.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
